# MindCastle Core Rules

- Preserve a calm, low-cognitive-load product direction in all decisions.
- Keep architecture future-proof: modular boundaries, typed interfaces, config-driven behavior.
- Avoid hardcoded product assumptions that block premium upgrades or customization.
- Theme customization is mandatory by default; no feature should assume a single theme.
- App should use full available screen space while respecting safe areas.
- The Castle is the visual anchor and must remain centered in the usable viewport.
- Prefer extensible abstractions over one-off implementations.